<subSubSection pageId="84" pageNumber="361" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="84.[2015,2608,2581,3004]" pageId="84" pageNumber="361">
Systematics and taxonomy of N. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1893" box="[2534,2608,2699,2728]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Neotoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="84" pageNumber="361" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="lepida">lepida</taxonomicName>
group was revisited for south-western USA and Mexico, resulting in relegation of several former species and subspecies into newly conceived N. 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Merriam" authorityYear="1887" box="[2330,2420,2857,2886]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Neotoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="84" pageNumber="361" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bryant">bryant</taxonomicName>
. Taxonomic status of N. 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Merriam" authorityYear="1887" box="[2185,2271,2892,2925]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Neotoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="84" pageNumber="361" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bryant">bryant</taxonomicName>
: has been resolved with genetic and morphometric methods. Five subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
